  "prompt": "Do you think the promise made by BJP of giving 15 lakhs to every Indians account will be true?",
  "response": "BJP, in the lead up to the 2014 General Elections, had promised to bring back black money stored in foreign accounts and distribute \u20b915 lakhs to every Indian citizen's account. The claim was made based on the assumption that there was a huge amount of undeclared and untaxed wealth (black money) stored in foreign banks by Indian citizens, which could be reclaimed and distributed to the public.\n\nHowever, after coming to power, the BJP-led government clarified that this promise was not meant to be taken literally, but rather as an illustrative example of how bringing back black money could benefit the country. The government argued that it was challenging to recover black money stored in foreign accounts, and the process was more complex than previously understood.\n\nIn reality, the promise of \u20b915 lakhs to every Indian citizen's account did not materialize. While the government has made efforts to curb black money and illicit financial flows, the complex and time-consuming nature of the process has made it difficult to fulfill the initial promise.\n\nIn conclusion, the promise of giving \u20b915 lakhs to every Indian's account has not been fulfilled and is unlikely to be realized in the near future. It is essential for voters to critically evaluate the claims made by political parties during election campaigns and consider the feasibility and practical implications of such promises.",
